description: DlOuterLoop: Downlink outer loop configuration parameters for different cells in a specific area at a given time.  dateTime: Timestamp of the configuration; Area_Name: Geographical area; CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site; Id2: Secondary cell identifier (potentially redundant with CellId); Id3: Further cell identification (e.g., sector); Id4: Auxiliary identifier; vsDataType: Data type identifier; vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format; DlOuterLoop.initValMixIpn: Initial value for mixed IPN; DlOuterLoop.dlOuterLoopId: Unique identifier for the outer loop configuration; DlOuterLoop.initValNonMixIpn: Initial value for non-mixed IPN; DlOuterLoop.largeStepNonMixIpn: Large step size for non-mixed IPN; DlOuterLoop.largeStepMixIpn: Large step size for mixed IPN; DlOuterLoop.dualOuterLoopEnabled: Boolean indicating if dual outer loop is enabled; DlOuterLoop.smallDownStep: Small step size for downlink.
